HEADWORD: Pichurim bean
<hw>Pich"u*rim bean`</hw> <pr>(p⟦icr⟧ch"⟦usl⟧*r⟦icr⟧m b⟦emac⟧n`)</pr>.
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The seed of a Brazilian lauraceous tree
(<spn>Nectandra Puchury</spn>) of a taste and smell between those of
nutmeg and of sassafras, -- sometimes used medicinally. Called also
<altname>sassafras nut</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pici</ent>⟦br⟧
